From 65a8d89a97167844dee754646ea7e41d80b4101c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 03:20:01 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 15/25] Existence proofs: pass/commit serialization and
 insertion edges
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Spec §4.4 tests 22, 24, 28 — the serialization fact cluster (§4.1 fact 2)
and the insertion edge (fact 4), the second no-existence-proof group the
spec orders before bindings (§8). All three PROVEN against current React:

- 22: a same-root urgent commit discards an older yielded same-root pass
  BEFORE any committed-view advance: the discard (pass-end) edge precedes
  the urgent commit report in the event log; the discarded pass's batch
  reaches the committed view exactly once, through a fresh pass started
  after the urgent commit.
- 24: an update inserted after a pass completed but had not committed
  (suspensey commit window: <ViewTransition> opts the subtree into
  SuspenseyImagesMode, so a pending suspensey-thing suspends the commit
  in the default channel) forces a PRE-commit restart: the urgent
  insertion commits first, the completed tree is discarded without ever
  reaching the committed view, the batch re-renders from scratch and
  commits once when the image resolves.
- 28: invariant across an interleaving with a yield gap: no root's
  committed view ever advances while that root has an open pass frame —
  and the invariant is per root (a cross-root commit inside another
  root's yield gap occurs and is allowed).

Channel semantics pinned as of this generation: the pass frame closes at
render completion or at the implicit discard; S3's yield/resume +
end-disposition edges extend the frame to the commit/discard edge and
build on exactly the discard-before-advance serialization proven here.
